memberdef.name: _NRFX_EVAL_IF_ENABLED
memberdef.initializer: NRFX_COND_CODE_1(NRFX_CONCAT(NRFX_, periph_name, prefix, i, _ENABLED), \ (macro(periph_name, prefix, i, __VA_ARGS__)), \ off_code)

detaileddescription.para: Used by NRFX_FOREACH_ENABLED. Execute provided macro if driver instance is enabled.

parameterdescription.para: Code which is pasted when given driver instance is disabled. Must be given in parentheses.
Prefix added before instance index, e.g. some device has instances named like SPIM00. First 0 is passed here as prefix.
Variable length arguments passed to the macro. Macro has following arguments: macro(periph_name, prefix, i, ...).

detaileddescription.para: Used by NRFX_FOREACH_PRESENT. Execute provided macro if instance is present.
Presence is determined by existing of token NRF_<instance> defined with wrapped in parenthesis value (see NRFX_INSTANCE_PRESENT), where <instance> is the concatenation of periph_name, prefix and i.

parameterdescription.para: Code which is pasted when given driver instance is disabled. Must be given in parentheses.
Prefix added before instance index, e.g. some device has instances named like SPIM00. First 0 is passed here as prefix.
Variable length arguments passed to the macro. Macro has following arguments: macro(periph_name, prefix, i, ...).
